04:06.246 --> 04:09.166
Are you fucking joking? What's going on?

04:10.333 --> 04:11.460
You're just slow, man.

04:12.544 --> 04:14.463
"I'm slow"? What do you mean, "I'm slow"?

04:14.546 --> 04:17.339
- He doesn't mean "slow."
- He said, "slow." Shut up, okay?

04:17.423 --> 04:20.218
- What do you mean?
- I haven't had a record out in a year.

04:20.302 --> 04:23.346
So? You're gettin' ready to cut an album.
We just booked a studio.

04:23.472 --> 04:25.891
Look, Interscope's got two songs
ready to go.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.268
And they're fuckin' good.

04:28.351 --> 04:31.354
But they're not yours.
I thought you want to do your own stuff.

04:31.438 --> 04:34.775
We've been telling you for a while now
that we need a new single, okay?

04:37.152 --> 04:39.237
Jesus. Elijah, come on, man.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.907
I got nothing but love for you, man.
Really.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.326
It's not personal.

04:46.953 --> 04:48.330
Yeah.

05:08.767 --> 05:10.185
Good morning, Eve.

05:11.895 --> 05:13.688
- Morning, Matt.
- Hi.

05:14.731 --> 05:17.108
- Does she know about...
- Everyone knows.

05:19.820 --> 05:22.197
Can you pull Elijah's sheet
when you get a chance?

05:23.114 --> 05:25.450
- Thanks.
- Matt Ryder's office. This is Kim.

05:25.534 --> 05:28.245
I'm sorry. Mr. Ryder is in a meeting.
Can you return?

05:28.328 --> 05:30.539
- Thank you.
- Shit. His numbers were holding.

05:30.622 --> 05:33.208
- Rob Marker's office. This is Kim.
- Rob Marker's office?

05:33.291 --> 05:36.545
I'm sorry. I don't have him right now.
Can you return? Great.

05:37.504 --> 05:40.465
- What the hell was that?
- Marker's been promoted.

05:40.715 --> 05:42.133
Really?

05:42.217 --> 05:45.053
And Mr. Lepselter
actually wants to see you right now.

05:47.722 --> 05:48.932
Sit down.

05:53.144 --> 05:54.729
Am I about to get fired?

05:55.355 --> 05:56.439
Sit down.

05:58.650 --> 06:02.612
I've been working for you since
before you could make payroll. Ten years.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.781
I've kept you on at a loss
for the last few.

06:04.865 --> 06:06.992
A loss? Really? Okay.

06:08.451 --> 06:11.663
I brought you a Coldplay demo in '99.
You didn't even listen to it.

06:11.746 --> 06:14.249
Arcade Fire in 2003.
A bootleg and you were like,

06:14.332 --> 06:16.960
"Great in concert.
Won't translate to the airwaves."

06:17.043 --> 06:20.839
Three years ago, I had the Spare Sevens
in the room. In the fucking room.

06:20.922 --> 06:24.759
I blew a few good calls for you. So?
You been cashin' that chit in for years.

06:24.843 --> 06:27.512
I know music better than anybody
in this fuckin' office.

06:27.596 --> 06:31.016
Yeah. You've got a great ear.
That made you irreplaceable in 1998.

06:31.099 --> 06:33.602
- Bullshit. It still matters.
- Music is a commodity.

06:33.685 --> 06:37.397
And it's airborne. You can't protect it.
You can't sell what you can't protect.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.400
You only sell the artist.
You haven't been signing any.

06:40.483 --> 06:43.778
Last night, you let your meal ticket
walk out that door.

06:44.905 --> 06:46.114
Yeah.

06:46.489 --> 06:48.033
Yeah, well...

06:48.992 --> 06:50.577
I'm still working 'em.

06:50.869 --> 06:53.288
- Working who?
- Spare Sevens.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.415
- Spare Sevens?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:55.582 --> 06:56.416
Right.

06:56.499 --> 07:00.629
Hey, I'm not jokin'. No, no, no.
They're not happy at Sony.

07:00.712 --> 07:03.006
The label rushed the last album.
They're pissed.

07:03.131 --> 07:05.133
The Spare Sevens
are about to pop globally.

07:05.216 --> 07:06.760
Sony will make them happy.

07:06.843 --> 07:08.553
No. These guys aren't like Elijah.

07:08.637 --> 07:12.766
They actually take the time to make music
the way real bands used to make it.

07:13.308 --> 07:16.144
I talked to their manager, Dan, at PMO.

07:17.020 --> 07:19.648
- You have a sit-down?
- I will.

07:24.611 --> 07:25.904
I'll give you two weeks.

07:25.987 --> 07:29.658
Not because I owe it to you,
but because I want the Spare Sevens.

07:44.422 --> 07:45.298
Hello.

07:47.676 --> 07:49.761
You have no pictures.

07:50.679 --> 07:53.848
Like, on your walls and your desk.
You don't have any photos.

07:53.932 --> 07:55.725
Who doesn't hang up a picture?

07:55.809 --> 07:57.978
Good question.
Here's another: Who are you?

07:58.061 --> 08:03.024
Most people in the office have photos of
their wife, girlfriend, dog. Something.

08:03.566 --> 08:07.570
Well, my wife left me, don't have
a girlfriend, and I'm afraid of dogs.

08:07.654 --> 08:09.489
I'm sorry to disappoint. Excuse me.

08:09.572 --> 08:11.491
<i>Yes?</i>

08:11.574 --> 08:14.744
Hi. There is a strange woman
standing in my office.

08:14.869 --> 08:16.955
- <i>On my way.</i>
- I am not strange.

08:17.038 --> 08:19.207
- You're a little strange.
- I work for Ben.

08:19.874 --> 08:22.877
Oh, oh, you work for Ben.
Okay, that's great.

08:22.961 --> 08:26.506
- I don't know who that is.
- Benjamin Asher Ryder.

08:26.589 --> 08:28.049
Your father.

08:30.135 --> 08:32.095
Sorry, I'm Zooey Kern.

08:32.178 --> 08:35.140
I'm Ben's nurse/personal assistant.

08:36.307 --> 08:39.394
Listen, Miss Kern. This has already been
a monumentally shitty day,

08:39.477 --> 08:41.813
and I haven't started dealing
with the West Coast.

08:41.895 --> 08:43.398
Hey, Kim!

08:43.481 --> 08:46.276
Not sure what you're doing here.
Honestly, I don't care.

08:46.359 --> 08:48.069
Ben's dying.

08:54.534 --> 08:57.954
Right. See, I thought I covered that
with "I don't care."

08:58.621 --> 09:00.957
- He has liver cancer.
- Uh-huh.

09:01.041 --> 09:04.627
And he's got three months left,
maybe four.

09:05.003 --> 09:08.590
Sorry, Matt. I was in with Marker.
Miss, do you have an appointment?

09:08.673 --> 09:11.426
- Wouldn't you know if she did?
- It was rhetorical.

09:11.509 --> 09:14.054
I need you to show this woman out. Okay?

09:14.137 --> 09:16.306
Then get ahold of Dan Summers
at PMO Talent.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.475
I want to talk to him
about the Spare Sevens.

09:18.558 --> 09:20.518
Actually, just say that it's urgent.

09:20.602 --> 09:22.771
- Rob Marker's office.
- Are you kidding me?

09:27.442 --> 09:29.360
I'll just call security myself.

09:29.444 --> 09:31.362
I don't think you actually have security.

09:32.447 --> 09:33.740
No. No, we don't.

09:33.823 --> 09:35.825
Are you familiar with Kodachrome?

09:37.243 --> 09:40.038
Yes. Paul Simon, 1973.
What do you want to know?

09:40.121 --> 09:41.623
Not that. Kodachrome film.

09:41.706 --> 09:45.460
Your father shoots on Kodachrome. He
prefers his pictures to be projected...

09:45.543 --> 09:47.962
...with light rather than printed.
I know his spiel.

09:48.046 --> 09:51.716
There's only one place left in the world
that processes Kodachrome,

09:51.800 --> 09:54.010
and that's Dwayne's Photo
in Parsons, Kansas.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.346
But Kodak decided to
stop manufacturing the dyes,

09:56.429 --> 09:59.766
so after next week, it'll be impossible
to develop Kodachrome film.

09:59.849 --> 10:01.643
- Amazing.
- Your father found four rolls

10:01.726 --> 10:03.061
he shot a long time ago,

10:03.144 --> 10:06.272
and he never got them developed,
and it woke something up in him.

10:06.356 --> 10:08.983
He's decided he's going to have
one last show.

10:09.067 --> 10:10.652
How about that? Good for him, okay?

10:10.735 --> 10:13.196
This has been very, very... annoying.

10:13.279 --> 10:15.573
- Let me show you out.
- Can I just...

10:16.366 --> 10:19.744
Ben needs to get these rolls to Kansas,
and he can't fly in his condition.

10:19.828 --> 10:22.330
If only there was a service
that delivered overnight.

10:22.413 --> 10:25.083
- Yeah, well, he doesn't trust FedEx.
- Of course not.

10:25.291 --> 10:29.546
You're his nurse/assistant/whatever.
Don't you have a driver's license?

10:29.629 --> 10:31.381
- Yeah, I do.
- There you go.

10:31.464 --> 10:34.634
But Ben wants you to drive him.

10:36.761 --> 10:37.971
Hmm.

10:38.054 --> 10:41.015
I'm gonna try to explain this
as clearly as possible for you.

10:41.516 --> 10:44.102
I've not spoken to the man
in over a decade.

10:44.227 --> 10:47.730
There's no way in hell I'm going
to Kansas with him. Or anywhere.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.232
Come to dinner tonight.

10:49.315 --> 10:51.151
I know I'm talking. I can hear my voice.

10:51.234 --> 10:52.360
Matt!

10:53.653 --> 10:55.697
He's dying.

10:57.949 --> 11:00.785
You should go see him one last time.

11:08.501 --> 11:11.546
There'll be a car waiting for you
downstairs.

11:42.827 --> 11:46.331
Hey, Matt. Larry Holdt, Ben's manager.

11:46.664 --> 11:47.957
Yeah, I remember you.

11:48.625 --> 11:51.669
The last time I saw you,
you were still a teenager.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.422
That's great.

11:56.216 --> 11:58.176
Well, maybe we should get inside.

12:16.611 --> 12:17.820
He's in there.

12:24.994 --> 12:27.455
<i>♪ You're so good ♪</i>

12:29.832 --> 12:31.834
<i>♪ You get me high ♪</i>

12:33.294 --> 12:36.089
- <i>Hey!</i>
- <i>♪ You're so good for me ♪</i>

12:38.383 --> 12:40.385
<i>♪ You're so good for me ♪</i>

12:59.821 --> 13:01.406
I didn't think you'd come.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.162
Those look familiar.

13:09.247 --> 13:11.207
Well, they should. They're yours.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.793
You wanna bang it around a little?

13:14.627 --> 13:17.171
- No, I don't play anymore.
- That's too bad.

13:18.589 --> 13:20.633
'Cause you used to be pretty good.

13:40.945 --> 13:42.488
Oh, sorry for the smell.

13:43.948 --> 13:47.285
You know, the meds they give me
give me gas.

14:16.731 --> 14:17.690
So, Matt...

14:18.691 --> 14:22.278
Larry tells me things haven't been going
so well for you at the record label.

14:23.029 --> 14:28.159
I was telling Ben that record labels can't
find a sustainable business model.

14:28.242 --> 14:31.454
You told me that he was gonna be
out on his ass any day now.

14:31.537 --> 14:32.663
Jesus, Ben.

14:32.747 --> 14:35.249
- Where'd you hear that?
- Larry knows everything.

14:35.333 --> 14:38.086
- Behave.
- I'm dyin'. I don't have time to behave.

14:38.878 --> 14:42.799
Come on. That's bullshit.
You were a prick long before cancer.

14:43.716 --> 14:45.093
That's true enough.

14:46.469 --> 14:48.805
At least you two are talking.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.139
This is good.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.478
So how much time you got left?

14:57.855 --> 15:00.108
Depends on which doctor you talk to.

15:00.441 --> 15:02.443
I'm betting tits up by New Year's.

15:04.278 --> 15:08.616
Why did you get divorced? She catch you
in flagrante with some other babe?

15:10.034 --> 15:12.203
- You'd like that, wouldn't you?
- You catch her?

15:12.286 --> 15:15.248
Because you fucked around on Mom
doesn't mean everyone does.

15:15.331 --> 15:16.624
Pace yourselves.

15:16.707 --> 15:19.085
Your mother and I had
a complicated relationship.

15:19.168 --> 15:22.004
Complicated by you putting your dick
in every woman you met.

15:22.130 --> 15:23.840
Your mother forgave me.

15:24.382 --> 15:27.427
- Yeah. Well, she died alone, Ben.
- So will I.

15:27.552 --> 15:29.512
- Yeah, but you deserve to.
- Hey.

15:34.350 --> 15:37.728
It's okay.
We're just... just catching up here.

15:37.812 --> 15:39.981
- People change.
- No, they don't.

15:41.399 --> 15:43.359
Why don't we talk about the trip?

15:43.443 --> 15:47.405
I can save us all a lot of trouble here.
I'm not going on any trip.

15:51.033 --> 15:52.702
You are a desperate old man.

15:53.953 --> 15:57.165
Tryin' to what?
Manufacture some bullshit redemption?

15:58.416 --> 15:59.584
Why?

15:59.667 --> 16:05.173
So you can pretend your empty, selfish
life was anything but meaningless?

16:07.008 --> 16:08.342
Thanks, but no thanks.

16:09.427 --> 16:13.973
Just so you know, when you are dead,
no one's gonna care that you're gone.

16:14.640 --> 16:17.351
I mean, maybe these two,
but you pay for them.

16:48.216 --> 16:50.676
- Hello?
- Matt, Larry Holdt.

16:50.760 --> 16:52.220
- Hey, Larry.
- <i>I want to discuss...</i>

17:03.022 --> 17:04.440
Come on, man.

17:06.526 --> 17:07.734
<i>Matt, don't hang up.</i>

17:07.818 --> 17:09.779
- Not gonna change my mind, Larry.
- <i>I know.</i>

17:09.862 --> 17:12.949
- <i>I'm gonna change it for you.</i>
- Oh, you are? Really? How?

17:13.031 --> 17:15.701
<i>Spare Sevens. I can get you a sit-down.</i>

17:18.454 --> 17:20.998
- Go on.
- <i>Their manager used to work for me.</i>

17:21.915 --> 17:24.377
<i>He says you've been calling all day.</i>

17:24.460 --> 17:28.548
They're going to be playing in Chicago
in a few days. Some radio station thing.

17:28.631 --> 17:30.550
<i>You can swing by on your way.</i>

17:30.675 --> 17:33.177
Wait. Hold on.
What do you mean on my way?

17:33.553 --> 17:35.555
You're talking about Kansas, yeah?

17:35.930 --> 17:38.307
Look. I don't know
how to make this any more clear.

17:38.391 --> 17:40.309
That's just not going to happen.

17:40.393 --> 17:43.479
Look. Ben needs the show,
and you need that meeting

17:44.063 --> 17:47.275
<i>And trust me.
This is the only way you'll get it.</i>

17:50.111 --> 17:52.363
I'm not going to go with him, Larry.

17:53.739 --> 17:55.241
It's not happening.

17:55.741 --> 17:57.493
Please, don't call back.

18:18.180 --> 18:19.682
Fuck.

18:38.409 --> 18:40.953
Good morning, Matthew.
Glad you reconsidered.

18:42.330 --> 18:44.040
So what's up with the Sevens?

18:44.123 --> 18:45.416
Show's Saturday.

18:46.542 --> 18:48.794
I'll make arrangements
for a meeting afterwards.

18:49.378 --> 18:50.796
Mm-hmm.

18:52.632 --> 18:55.384
Still drive that, huh?
You fix the roof yet?

18:55.468 --> 18:57.720
I'm sorry.
Would you like to take your car?

18:58.346 --> 19:01.015
- I don't have a car.
- Then that settles that.

19:01.098 --> 19:03.017
The car runs fine, Matt.

19:03.851 --> 19:07.563
- You're going too, huh?
- Unless you want to give me my shots.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.566
- Is that okay with you?
- Fine with me.

19:12.401 --> 19:15.780
- All right.
- Let's go! We're burning daylight.

19:17.531 --> 19:20.993
<i>In two miles, merge onto I-80 West.</i>

19:21.077 --> 19:22.787
Do not text and drive, please.

19:22.870 --> 19:26.707
I'm not texting. I'm looking at texts.
There's a difference.

19:26.832 --> 19:30.211
Hey, this car doesn't have an iPhone jack
or anything like that, does it?

19:30.336 --> 19:34.423
We're strictly analog here.
Some cassettes in the glove compartment.

19:35.132 --> 19:39.804
<i>In 1.5 miles, stay
to the right to merge onto I-80 West.</i>

19:39.887 --> 19:42.348
Zooey, hand me that thing for a second,
will you?

19:42.431 --> 19:44.225
Yeah.

19:48.187 --> 19:52.066
- What the hell are you doing?
- Like I said, strictly analog.

19:52.191 --> 19:54.443
We gotta drive halfway
across the country.

19:54.527 --> 19:57.863
That's right. I'm not gonna have
some robot bitch whinin' in my ear,

19:57.947 --> 20:00.533
sending me on some sterile interstate.

20:00.616 --> 20:04.578
We have a week to get to Kansas.
We're taking the scenic route.

20:05.246 --> 20:07.206
We're going to use this map here.

20:07.707 --> 20:10.835
- Remember what a map is?
- Yeah. I know what a map is.

20:14.088 --> 20:15.798
- Turn that up, will you, Zo?
- Yeah.

20:15.881 --> 20:17.383
Love this song.

20:17.466 --> 20:23.472
<i>♪ You've already burned it down ♪</i>

20:25.141 --> 20:27.393
- What are you doing?
- Nothing.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.337
Ben, you're here.

21:04.555 --> 21:08.309
There's a diner across the street.
We should meet up later and grab dinner.

21:08.476 --> 21:10.436
That sounds like a plan.

21:11.228 --> 21:12.646
Yeah, you guys go ahead.

21:13.063 --> 21:16.776
I'm just gonna get in a quick workout,
make it an early night.

21:27.119 --> 21:28.370
Hey.

21:29.997 --> 21:31.791
Don't give me that look.

21:31.874 --> 21:35.669
Okay. You know what?
You need to let your guard down.

21:37.171 --> 21:40.174
- Excuse me?
- Yeah. I know you're scared.

21:40.257 --> 21:42.134
Scared? What am I scared of exactly?

21:42.218 --> 21:44.220
You're scared to open yourself up to him.

21:44.303 --> 21:46.806
You're scared to let yourself
love him again.

21:48.265 --> 21:49.683
- Wow.
- Don't.

21:49.767 --> 21:52.228
- Wow, that's amazing.
- Yeah. Mm-hmm.

21:52.353 --> 21:55.898
Yeah, I mean forget therapy
or the facts of my relationship with him,

21:55.981 --> 21:59.276
you spend six hours in a car with me,
and you've cracked the code.

21:59.360 --> 22:02.154
- You don't have to be a dick.
- No, I don't need to be a dick.

22:02.238 --> 22:05.074
I need to be...
less scared to let him in.

22:05.699 --> 22:06.992
Or let him into...

22:07.409 --> 22:09.870
- I'm just saying...
- I'll mull it over.

22:09.954 --> 22:11.622
You made the effort to come.

22:11.705 --> 22:14.959
You may as well
try and get to know him a little bit.

22:15.042 --> 22:16.335
Watch your fingers.

22:55.666 --> 22:59.378
<i>♪ I'd like to hold your hand ♪</i>

23:00.963 --> 23:02.381
Ahh!

23:02.464 --> 23:06.886
<i>♪ But your hand isn't here anymore ♪</i>

23:11.223 --> 23:14.643
<i>♪ I'd like to see your eyes ♪</i>

23:18.147 --> 23:23.777
<i>♪ But your eyes do not see any longer ♪</i>

23:26.864 --> 23:30.784
<i>♪ I want to walk with you ♪</i>

23:33.579 --> 23:38.500
<i>♪ But our walks do not exist any longer ♪</i>

23:42.171 --> 23:46.133
<i>♪ No, your eyes do not see anymor</i> e ♪

23:47.217 --> 23:49.053
<i>It was 1998 or so,</i>

23:49.136 --> 23:53.515
and I was in the White House doing
a spread on Clinton at Bill's request.

23:53.891 --> 23:57.519
It was right after the whole, you know,
bullshit impeachment circus.

23:57.603 --> 23:58.896
Bill was trying to prove...

23:58.979 --> 24:01.065
You're calling
the Lewinsky scandal bullshit?

24:01.148 --> 24:04.193
He cheated on his wife
and lied to the entire country about it.

24:04.276 --> 24:07.404
They all cheat. They all fuck around.
You should know that.

24:07.529 --> 24:10.157
- Ben.
- What? After the way your marriage ended?

24:10.240 --> 24:12.326
- You're seriously gonna sit here and...
- Stop.

24:12.409 --> 24:16.163
What? Just because Matt's here.
Don't be an idiot.

24:16.246 --> 24:20.501
- If anybody knows about fuckin' around...
- Hey, you need to stop talking now.

24:21.335 --> 24:23.671
- Leave her alone, okay?
- It's fine.

24:25.047 --> 24:27.091
I do believe Matt here's defending you.

24:27.633 --> 24:31.303
Just go back to your bullshit stories
about you and your fancy friends.

24:31.387 --> 24:33.806
What we're seeing now is jealousy.

24:34.431 --> 24:39.728
Envy and resentment of a man living in the
shadow of his father's accomplishments.

24:40.479 --> 24:42.815
Yeah, you've had a great big life.

24:43.357 --> 24:45.484
- Yeah. You're damn straight I did.
- Mm-hmm.

24:47.111 --> 24:49.238
Where are all those friends
while you're dying?

24:49.321 --> 24:50.197
- Matt.
- Alone?

24:50.280 --> 24:51.323
Stop.

24:51.407 --> 24:56.161
My work will live on long after I'm gone.
What have you done?

25:02.668 --> 25:06.880
Holy shit. Look at that, man.
She's gotta be 250 pounds or something.

25:07.172 --> 25:08.799
That outfit's beautiful.

25:12.261 --> 25:14.388
Can you just try and take it easy on him?

25:14.471 --> 25:17.057
Me? Are you kidding me?
I was defending you.

25:17.141 --> 25:23.814
You know, a month from now, two months,
he's going to be gone forever.

25:23.897 --> 25:26.567
No, I get it, okay?
I understand the concept.

25:26.650 --> 25:29.862
It doesn't give him a free pass
to be an asshole to people.

25:32.156 --> 25:34.575
'Kay.

25:35.034 --> 25:37.077
I'm going to go back to the motel.

25:41.957 --> 25:43.542
Boy.

25:44.084 --> 25:46.462
- Fucking...
- Here's your check, hon.

25:47.296 --> 25:48.714
Yeah. Thanks.

25:58.474 --> 26:02.728
<i>♪ Yes, I understand
That every life must end ♪</i>

26:02.811 --> 26:04.813
<i>♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>

26:07.483 --> 26:13.072
<i>♪ As we sit alone
I know someday we must go, oh ♪</i>

26:16.241 --> 26:22.081
<i>♪ Oh, I'm a lucky man
To count on both hands the ones I love ♪</i>

26:25.167 --> 26:31.173
<i>♪ Some folks just have one
Yeah, others they got none, uh-huh ♪</i>

26:34.343 --> 26:37.638
<i>♪ Stay with me ♪</i>

26:37.721 --> 26:42.309
<i>♪ Oh, let's just breathe ♪</i>

26:47.314 --> 26:50.776
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

26:52.903 --> 26:57.908
<i>♪ Practiced on our sins
Never gonna let me win, oh ♪</i>

27:05.457 --> 27:07.292
What? What's funny?

27:09.545 --> 27:11.004
Uh...

27:12.297 --> 27:16.176
When I was a kid,
my mom used to take me up to the Poconos

27:16.260 --> 27:18.137
for a few weeks every summer.

27:18.220 --> 27:22.391
After we'd pass a few of those
deer crossing signs that just went by,

27:23.642 --> 27:25.102
I remember I asked her,

27:26.186 --> 27:30.983
"Mom, how do the deers know
that's where they're supposed to cross?"

27:32.442 --> 27:34.403
I was being serious. I was a kid.

27:34.820 --> 27:39.950
But she just laughed her ass off like
it was the funniest thing she ever heard.

27:40.742 --> 27:42.286
That felt great, 'cause...

27:43.954 --> 27:46.248
I don't remember her laughing much.

27:50.085 --> 27:51.336
When did she die?

27:54.381 --> 27:55.674
I...

27:57.759 --> 27:59.511
When I was 13.

28:02.639 --> 28:04.725
I'm so sorry.

28:08.520 --> 28:13.692
After that I moved out of New York to
live with my aunt and uncle in Cleveland.

28:15.152 --> 28:18.530
Ben was...
He was working in Africa at the time.

28:20.532 --> 28:23.202
He didn't even make it back
for the funeral.

28:23.327 --> 28:25.579
There was a civil war going on.

28:25.662 --> 28:26.914
Mm-hmm.

28:26.997 --> 28:29.499
I'm not making excuses. I'm just...

28:30.584 --> 28:34.796
saying if you think you had it rough,
just spend some time and effort.

28:34.922 --> 28:36.757
I'll remember that.

28:40.594 --> 28:42.221
We should go see him.

28:43.055 --> 28:43.889
Go see who?

28:44.556 --> 28:47.768
Your Uncle Dean.
Cleveland's only an hour away,

28:47.851 --> 28:51.355
and your "Spare Sister's" thing
isn't until tomorrow night.

28:52.231 --> 28:54.358
I wouldn't mind seeing my brother...

28:55.234 --> 28:58.070
one more time before I leave this planet.

28:59.154 --> 29:00.447
Yeah, but...

29:01.031 --> 29:02.741
Dean hates you.

29:03.951 --> 29:06.787
He doesn't hate me.
He's just pissed off at me.

29:10.499 --> 29:14.419
<i>♪ Nothing you would take ♪</i>

29:14.503 --> 29:18.507
<i>♪ Everything you gave ♪</i>

29:19.007 --> 29:22.177
<i>♪ Oh, hold me 'till I die ♪</i>

29:22.928 --> 29:27.933
<i>♪ Meet you on the other side ♪</i>

29:39.820 --> 29:41.280
I'll be damned.

29:41.947 --> 29:42.948
Hi, Dean.

29:45.325 --> 29:46.535
You dyin'?

29:46.618 --> 29:49.413
- What? Is it that obvious?
- Well, you're here.

29:50.831 --> 29:51.999
Yes, I am

29:53.667 --> 29:55.168
It's good to see you

29:57.129 --> 30:00.882
- Matt, what are you doin' here?
- Hi. That is a long story.

30:00.966 --> 30:02.092
Yeah, I bet.

30:02.759 --> 30:05.053
- And who's this?
- This is Zooey.

30:05.137 --> 30:06.930
- Yep, Zooey.
- Is that Matty?

30:07.014 --> 30:08.140
Nice to meet you.

30:08.223 --> 30:09.641
- Hi!
- Hey.

30:11.560 --> 30:12.728
Ben.

30:13.228 --> 30:15.856
- Hi, Sarah.
- He's dying.

30:16.106 --> 30:19.026
Well, not in our driveway, he isn't.
Bring him on in.

30:19.109 --> 30:22.154
And you!
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

30:22.237 --> 30:24.031
Sorry. It was a last-minute thing.

30:24.114 --> 30:26.700
- Hey! Hi!
- This is Zooey.

30:26.783 --> 30:29.828
Oh, Matty. Well, now she's more like it.

30:29.911 --> 30:32.414
I mean,
I told him not to marry the other one.

30:32.497 --> 30:36.084
- No, I, um...
- Zooey is Ben's nurse.

30:37.336 --> 30:40.255
Oh, because your auras are conjoined.

30:40.339 --> 30:43.175
- I could see that immediately
- Yeah. Yeah.

30:43.425 --> 30:46.511
Aunt Sarah here can see auras.

30:46.595 --> 30:49.014
- And she can hear sarcasm.
- Of course she can.

30:49.097 --> 30:51.600
- You guys are gonna spend the night?
- If that's okay.

30:51.683 --> 30:53.894
Great.
Matty, you and Zooey take your old room.

30:53.977 --> 30:56.063
- But we are... not together.
- Nope.

31:08.450 --> 31:09.451
Hi.

31:10.577 --> 31:12.371
- Hey.
- This was your room.

31:12.454 --> 31:16.750
Yeah. Basically, seventh, eighth grade
through high school.

31:17.000 --> 31:19.211
God, you were really into music.

31:19.711 --> 31:24.466
Yep. They say it's the one thing
I inherited from Ben.

31:26.927 --> 31:31.640
Actually, I would say that
the only memories, or good ones,

31:31.723 --> 31:35.185
at least, that I have of him
were listening to music.

31:35.268 --> 31:39.189
We had this little den
and this old Fisher stereo.

31:39.314 --> 31:41.358
I mean, new at the time, but...

31:41.441 --> 31:44.528
He'd let me play records
when he was goin' through the slides.

31:44.611 --> 31:45.612
Mm-hmm.

31:45.695 --> 31:49.074
So, while most kids had people
singin' 'em lullabies to sleep,

31:49.157 --> 31:52.494
I had Graham Nash singing "Wounded Bird."

31:53.453 --> 31:55.330
Let's see what we have here.

31:55.622 --> 31:59.459
Ooh! Pearl Jam. Radiohead.

31:59.543 --> 32:02.629
- Nirvana.
- What can I say? I was a moody kid.

32:02.712 --> 32:06.466
Yeah, you can tell a lot about someone's
past from the music they listened to.

32:07.384 --> 32:09.928
Then I guess you know a lot about
my past now.

32:10.846 --> 32:12.931
What do you think I listened to?

32:15.851 --> 32:19.938
Very interesting question.
Okay, I'll bite.

32:20.814 --> 32:23.358
But in order to do this
to the best of my ability,

32:23.442 --> 32:26.570
I have to actually figure out
your exact age, so... excuse this.

32:26.653 --> 32:30.073
This might be a little rude.
What are you? Twenty-eight?

32:30.699 --> 32:31.867
- I'm 30.
- You are?

32:31.950 --> 32:32.826
- Yeah.
- Hey.

32:32.909 --> 32:34.786
- Thank you.
- Dodged a bullet there.

32:35.996 --> 32:39.916
So that means you were
a freshman in college, like, in 2000.

32:40.625 --> 32:43.503
So then you were into...

32:44.171 --> 32:47.048
Sorry to say, but you're a product
of your environment. Top 40.

32:47.132 --> 32:50.510
I'm talking Britney, Christina,
boy bands, N'SYNC, Backstreet Boys,

32:50.594 --> 32:52.345
maybe Alanis when you're feeling dark.

32:52.429 --> 32:54.473
- Please give me some credit.
- But then...

32:54.556 --> 32:57.893
But then you started to rebel against
your middle-class suburban values.

32:57.976 --> 33:00.145
- Is that what I was doing?
- Mm-hmm.

33:00.228 --> 33:03.190
Or possibly
you met a guy into alternative music.

33:03.273 --> 33:07.569
Why do you assume that I changed
for a guy? Maybe he changed for me.

33:07.652 --> 33:11.364
No, no. Guys don't change for girls.
Not in college at least.

33:11.615 --> 33:13.950
- When do they change then?
- Much later.

33:15.494 --> 33:17.120
Usually when it's too late.

33:18.538 --> 33:21.666
You started to listen to bands
you thought would make you edgier,

33:21.750 --> 33:24.419
but you're still hopelessly mainstream.

33:24.503 --> 33:27.881
You're sittin' there in your dorm room,
and you're listening to...

33:29.216 --> 33:30.175
Live.

33:32.219 --> 33:34.137
Like who live? What live?

33:34.221 --> 33:37.557
- No, the band, "Live."
- I don't know of a band called Live.

33:37.641 --> 33:39.059
Live. You know. Like...

33:39.142 --> 33:40.519
<i>♪ I alone want you ♪</i>

33:40.602 --> 33:44.064
I actually could not name a single song
that the band Live had.

33:44.147 --> 33:46.733
What about "Lightning Crashes"?
Everyone knows that.

33:46.858 --> 33:48.610
<i>♪ Her placenta falls to the floor ♪</i>

33:48.735 --> 33:50.403
- Oh, my God!
- What?

33:50.487 --> 33:53.990
People know it because it's the only
pop song with the word "placenta" in it.

33:54.074 --> 33:57.869
You're really bad at this.
I was a weird, sad punk.

33:57.953 --> 34:00.413
- It was the Smiths, Pixies.
- But you loved Live.

34:00.497 --> 34:03.583
- Yeah, I loved Live.
- Biggest fan. Live's biggest fan.

34:03.667 --> 34:04.876
No, I'm not wrong.

34:05.794 --> 34:07.671
- This isn't bad.
- What?

34:07.754 --> 34:09.755
- Galaxie 500.
- Oh, yeah.

34:09.839 --> 34:11.424
- Obscure.
- Indeed.

34:11.507 --> 34:14.469
- Does your record player still work?
- Fucking better.

34:14.886 --> 34:17.013
Let's take it for a spin.

34:24.646 --> 34:28.984
<i>♪ My head will turn to yellow ♪</i>

34:29.400 --> 34:34.697
<i>♪ My eyes will turn to green ♪</i>

34:35.907 --> 34:40.245
<i>♪ My voice will turn to mellow ♪</i>

34:40.328 --> 34:46.333
<i>♪ But still I can't be seen ♪</i>

34:47.877 --> 34:52.382
<i>♪ Melt away ♪</i>

34:52.465 --> 34:57.596
<i>♪ I want to melt away ♪</i>

34:59.222 --> 35:03.685
<i>♪ Melt away ♪</i>

35:03.768 --> 35:09.149
<i>♪ I want to melt away ♪</i>

35:13.778 --> 35:17.032
How is Hank? Is he married?
Is Hank married yet?

35:17.115 --> 35:19.159
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Couple of years now.

35:19.242 --> 35:21.703
- Have any kids?
- Not yet, but...

35:21.786 --> 35:24.706
You know, they're so young.
There's no rush.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.710
So what's so special about
these photographs

35:28.793 --> 35:32.130
you need to drive halfway
across the country to get them developed?

35:32.213 --> 35:34.382
It's some of my early work.

35:34.466 --> 35:35.842
Stuff I shot years ago.

35:36.593 --> 35:39.054
What happens if you get 'em back,
and they're garbage?

35:39.137 --> 35:40.805
How do you even know what's on them?

35:40.889 --> 35:43.266
I remember every shot I've ever taken.

35:44.184 --> 35:47.020
That's, like,
hundreds of thousands of photos.

35:47.145 --> 35:49.773
- You remember all of them?
- Yep.

35:50.315 --> 35:51.983
That's impressive.

35:53.818 --> 35:55.320
When's my birthday?

36:03.828 --> 36:06.539
- February 19.
- February 19.

36:07.165 --> 36:09.626
You got it. Yeah.

36:21.137 --> 36:23.056
- Last one.
- Thanks.

36:23.139 --> 36:25.684
It's good to see them together again.

36:27.352 --> 36:29.354
It's good to see you with him.

36:31.815 --> 36:34.484
I don't know. He left us.

36:35.568 --> 36:37.445
Hell, he left you guys too.

36:38.530 --> 36:42.617
Now he's dying, so he comes back,
and we're just lettin' him back in.

36:44.035 --> 36:46.287
It's like he's getting away with it.

36:46.413 --> 36:47.872
Matty, look at him.

36:49.082 --> 36:52.627
I mean, does that look like a man
who's gotten away with anything?

36:57.340 --> 36:58.842
Mmm.

36:58.967 --> 37:00.218
Okay, I'm gonna...

37:01.553 --> 37:02.887
I'm gonna go upstairs.

37:03.263 --> 37:05.724
Try and get a little work done
before I pass out.

37:08.226 --> 37:11.479
Can I take this, put wine it,
and drink it in my room?

37:11.563 --> 37:13.273
- Help yourself.
- All right.

37:13.690 --> 37:15.567
- 'Night, sweetheart.
- 'Night.

37:15.859 --> 37:17.444
- I'm so glad you're here.
- Me too.

37:17.527 --> 37:19.404
- I love you.
- Love you too.

37:23.616 --> 37:26.369
Hey, guys. I'm going to bed.
I'll see you in the morning.

37:26.453 --> 37:28.163
- Okay.
- All right.

37:35.128 --> 37:37.338
- You good?
- Yeah.

37:37.422 --> 37:40.759
Yeah, no, I'm just a little tired.
Gonna get some work done.

37:41.718 --> 37:43.720
I'm glad you're making this trip.

37:44.721 --> 37:48.224
A man should know his father,
no matter what kind of bastard he is.

37:52.812 --> 37:54.814
You should come back here more often.

37:54.898 --> 37:58.693
- I know. I'm sorry.
- That's okay. End of the lecture.

37:58.777 --> 38:00.487
- It's good to see you.
- Thanks.

38:13.166 --> 38:14.292
Yep.

38:14.959 --> 38:16.878
- Hey, I saw...
- Hey.

38:17.128 --> 38:20.507
that your light was still on.
I got you a glass of water.

38:20.590 --> 38:21.591
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

38:21.674 --> 38:23.676
I know those guys can drink, so...

38:23.760 --> 38:26.054
Thought that might help
the cause in the morning.

38:26.137 --> 38:27.931
- How are you?
- Good.

38:28.223 --> 38:29.891
Is it hard being here?

38:31.893 --> 38:32.852
Um...

38:33.186 --> 38:35.772
- Sorry. Do you want to come in?
- Yeah.

38:37.315 --> 38:40.485
No. I mean, me, no.

38:41.319 --> 38:43.488
- Um, can I sit down?
- Yeah.

38:45.031 --> 38:48.243
Not weird for me. I guess
the weird thing would be...

38:50.203 --> 38:52.580
you know, seein' Ben here.

38:52.664 --> 38:55.041
Is a little, you know, odd.

39:02.090 --> 39:03.007
Oh, um...

39:03.883 --> 39:06.511
Sarah... thinks you're beautiful.

39:09.013 --> 39:11.474
Okay. Cool.

39:15.436 --> 39:16.771
You are though.

39:18.940 --> 39:21.734
- I think you're drunk.
- No.

39:23.611 --> 39:26.656
Maybe. I might be, actually.

39:26.739 --> 39:29.284
But I'm not saying this 'cause I'm drunk.

39:29.367 --> 39:30.952
And I'm not gonna not say it

39:31.035 --> 39:33.997
'cause I think you'll think
I'm only saying it because I'm drunk.

39:34.497 --> 39:36.291
I don't know what we're talking about.

39:36.374 --> 39:38.376
- Oh, you didn't follow that?
- No.

39:38.543 --> 39:41.754
Then maybe I am drunk.
'Cause I followed it perfectly.

39:44.215 --> 39:46.759
Oh, this is a bad idea.

39:47.552 --> 39:49.721
- What? We're just talking.
- Yeah, well.

39:49.804 --> 39:55.310
Then you have to talk about the fact that
you're just talking and not just talking.

39:56.102 --> 39:57.061
Right.

40:02.609 --> 40:05.445
- Wait, I'm sorry. I mean...
- Oh! Whoa.

40:05.570 --> 40:08.448
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.

40:09.032 --> 40:10.700
Holy shit.

40:10.783 --> 40:12.869
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

40:12.952 --> 40:14.203
I guess I deserved that.

40:16.623 --> 40:19.792
Thanks.

40:22.003 --> 40:25.632
- Oh, hey, close your eyes.
- Are you gonna get weird?

40:26.507 --> 40:29.135
No. No. Just close 'em.

40:29.802 --> 40:31.554
Okay. They're closed.

40:31.638 --> 40:33.348
Hold on a sec.

40:37.101 --> 40:38.770
Okay, you can open 'em now.

40:40.521 --> 40:42.982
Wow. That's really cool.

40:44.692 --> 40:47.654
Yeah, my cousin Hank
was really into astronomy.

40:47.904 --> 40:49.989
Yeah, I can tell.

40:57.121 --> 40:59.958
- What, um, Ben was saying...
- Mm-hmm.

41:00.625 --> 41:04.170
...last night at the diner
about your... ex-husband?

41:07.131 --> 41:09.884
Is that what happened? He cheated?

41:13.346 --> 41:17.225
Nothing good comes from reliving the past.
You know?

41:19.268 --> 41:21.646
You just sound like my ex-wife now.

41:24.315 --> 41:26.234
She used to say that I'd...

41:27.735 --> 41:32.490
I had a tendency to live in the past
rather than... embracing the present.

41:34.826 --> 41:36.411
Is that why she left you?

41:40.248 --> 41:42.917
It's never... one thing, now, is it?

41:44.585 --> 41:46.045
What about you?

41:46.421 --> 41:49.424
I don't know.
It all just happened so fucking fast.

41:49.507 --> 41:53.636
One moment we're just...
we're cruising and then...

41:55.847 --> 41:58.141
the next we're driving off a cliff.

42:00.143 --> 42:02.270
The funny thing is, I actually...

42:03.438 --> 42:07.233
For a moment there,
I thought I had it together, you know?

42:09.318 --> 42:11.988
I thought
I was someone to be reckoned with.

42:31.632 --> 42:34.343
Oh, my God, Ben. Jesus.

42:35.720 --> 42:40.058
- Help. Oh, God.
- Ben, what did you do? Are you okay?

42:40.141 --> 42:45.730
Yeah, yeah. I just...
I just got dizzy, and I tripped over...

42:46.355 --> 42:48.858
the corner over here.
I was gonna take a shower.

42:48.941 --> 42:52.820
Wait for me before you do that.
Can you move your fingers? Toes?

42:53.154 --> 42:54.781
- Yeah.
- Any dizziness or nausea?

42:56.574 --> 42:58.743
- Do you have any pain?
- No.

42:59.118 --> 43:00.578
Bend your leg for me.

43:00.661 --> 43:06.375
Wait. Stop gropin' me. Jesus Christ.
What are you doin'?

43:06.459 --> 43:08.669
I need to make sure
you don't have broken bones.

43:08.753 --> 43:10.671
- Help me up.
- I got you.

43:11.422 --> 43:14.717
- Here you go.
- Oh, God. Jesus Christ.

43:14.801 --> 43:17.011
- You don't feel pain anywhere?
